This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and information extraction. The paper also mentions recent advances in learning text representations, which is a common topic in cs.CL. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper discusses building general purpose relation extractors, which is a common topic in AI research. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper mentions using machine learning techniques to build task agnostic relation representations. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category as the paper deals with information extraction from text. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper mentions using BERT, a neural network-based language model, for learning text representations.
